PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F163A1778159475
OL,1,Wj5hw1~{4k7juhw1{$             G2/2
OL,2,W+.-'"-$/*%*%*%/"-$/*%Q,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,3,GUK long range forecast
OL,4,
OL,5,COutlook for Thu 21 May to Thu 4 JunFLow
OL,6,Fpressure systems are likely to still
OL,7,Fbe close by to the UK at the start of
OL,8,Fthis period. This means showers or
OL,9,Flonger spells of rain are likely at
OL,10,Ftimes, these heavy in places, with the
OL,11,Fwettest conditions probably towards
OL,12,Fthe northwest by this stage. There
OL,13,Fwill, however, probably be some dry
OL,14,Fand warm interludes, these more likely
OL,15,Ftowards the south, although
OL,16,Ftemperatures are likely to be close to
OL,17,Fnormal overall. Later in the period,
OL,18,Fmore settled and drier conditions may
OL,19,Fdevelop, as high pressure establishes
OL,20,Fitself over or to the west of the UK,
OL,21,Fwith temperatures perhaps rising a
OL,22,Flittle above normal, especially in the
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,23,Fwest. Should this happen, eastern
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
OL,24,Fparts may be on the cool side with a
OL,25,Fpredominant flow off the North Sea.
